{"article_id":"gc4515ABn394QpUX","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Texas Sen. Ted Cruz","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"( R )","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"and his Democratic challenger Rep. Beto O ' Rourke just had what was likely to be their last face-to-face debate before the November 6 midterm elections .","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"As they sparred over Medicare-for-all , the GOP tax cuts , and border security ,","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"both candidates continued to try to appeal to their bases in a race","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"that has captured national attention and money","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"and built up long-held Democratic hopes","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"of turning Texas blue .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"Cruz argued","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"that O ' Rourke is dangerously liberal ,","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"while O ' Rourke called Cruz out-of-step and beholden to Republican donors .","depth":5},{"id":11,"text":"Cruz emphasized","depth":5},{"id":12,"text":"that O ' Rourke is too \" radical \" for Texas","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"- trying to paint him as more to the left than progressive Sens . Elizabeth Warren","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"( D-MA )","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"and Bernie Sanders","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"( I-VT ) .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"O ' Rourke , on the other hand , repeatedly called Cruz a liar","depth":5},{"id":18,"text":"and accused him of taking votes","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"to please Republican donors","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"rather than working for the people of Texas .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"He even adopted a nickname from President Trump :","depth":5},{"id":22,"text":"\" Sen . Cruz is not going to be honest with you , \"","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"O ' Rourke said at one point .","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"\" He ' s dishonest ,","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"that ' s why the president called him ' lying Ted , '","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"and that ' s why the nickname stuck ,","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"it ' s true . \"","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"O ' Rourke raised eye-popping $ 38 million in just three months , the most of any Senate candidate .","depth":6},{"id":29,"text":"There is undeniable hype surrounding his candidacy .","depth":6},{"id":30,"text":"But he is still the underdog in deep-red Texas .","depth":5},{"id":31,"text":"Even though some polling has shown the race in close single digits ,","depth":5},{"id":32,"text":"Cruz has been in the lead in every single poll","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"and is currently leading by 7 points ,","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"according to RealClearPolitics .","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"O ' Rourke still has another televised town hall with CNN","depth":5},{"id":36,"text":"that Cruz has said","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"he won ' t attend ,","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"so Tuesday night ' s debate was the last chance","depth":5},{"id":39,"text":"for both candidates to be on stage","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"and make their closing arguments together .","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"1 ) Cruz is challenged on his vote for GOP tax cuts","depth":4},{"id":42,"text":"- and O ' Rourke paints him as corrupt","depth":4},{"id":43,"text":"The sweeping GOP tax cuts became a moment of contention in the Texas Senate debate","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"when Cruz was asked by moderator Jason Whitely to square his longtime stance","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"to not increase the national deficit","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"with voting for a GOP tax bill","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"that is projected to increase the national deficit by more than $ 1 trillion .","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"Over his career in the Senate , Cruz was a noted critic of government spending under the Obama administration ,","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"calling it \" immoral \" spending","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"that would add to the national debt .","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"But","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"when it came for Republicans running deficits ,","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"Cruz went on the defense .","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"\" I ' m proud to have supported the tax cut ,","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"the tax cut is producing enormous benefits for the state of Texas and for the country , \"","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"Cruz responded .","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"Soon after , Whitely challenged Cruz","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"by asking about the projection of the Congressional Budget Office , Joint Committee on Taxation , and other nonpartisan groups","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"that the tax cut will in fact add $ 1.6 trillion to the deficit over the next 10 years .","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"\" No it wouldn ' t -","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"that projection is wrong , \"","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"Cruz said .","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"\" The reason","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"we have deficit and debt","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"is not because we cut taxes","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"and grow the economy .","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"We need to control the out-of-control spending","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"by cutting things like socialized medicine . \"","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"O ' Rourke used the opportunity","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"to paint Cruz as corrupt ,","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"he voted for tax cuts and other Republican bills at the direction of donors and PACs","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"- and highlighting his own pledge","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"not to take PAC money .","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"\" Follow the money , \"","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"O ' Rourke said .","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"\" Those tax cuts will disproportionately flow to corporations","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"who are already sitting on record piles of cash in a country","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"that is riven with income inequality","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"unseen seen since the last Gilded Age . \"","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"O ' Rourke is running as a progressive candidate in Texas ,","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"and Cruz seized on that .","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"Cruz wanted voters","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"who watched Tuesday ' s debate","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"to believe","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"O ' Rourke ' s vision for America was one with socialized medicine","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"bogged down by long wait times , extremely high costs for the government , and open borders","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"that would lead to immigrants","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"streaming into the US .","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"Cruz ' s stance on immigration is largely focused on securing the border .","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"He ' s interested in expanding H1-B visas for skilled immigrants","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"but railed against amnesty for immigrants","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"who arrived in the US illegally .","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"O ' Rourke , on the other hand , wants to pass the DREAM Act","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"and provide a path to citizenship for DREAMers , the young unauthorized immigrants","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"who were brought to the US illegally as children .","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"When it came to the immigration issue ,","depth":13},{"id":98,"text":"Cruz played to fears about crime south of the border ,","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"saying","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"O ' Rourke opposed even the most basic border security .","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"\" Congressman O ' Rourke not only opposes a wall ...","depth":15},{"id":102,"text":"he wants to tear down the ones","depth":16},{"id":103,"text":"we have , \"","depth":16},{"id":104,"text":"Cruz said ,","depth":14},{"id":105,"text":"noting the wall between O ' Rourke ' s hometown of El Paso , Texas , and neighboring Juarez , Mexico .","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"\" There ' s a wall there ,","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"that wall is one of the tools","depth":14},{"id":108,"text":"you use","depth":15},{"id":109,"text":"to protect us . \"","depth":15},{"id":110,"text":"O ' Rourke shot back ,","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"saying","depth":13},{"id":112,"text":"the immigration policy","depth":16},{"id":113,"text":"he supports","depth":16},{"id":114,"text":"is about more than border walls","depth":15},{"id":115,"text":"- including a pathway to citizenship DREAMers .","depth":14},{"id":116,"text":"\" I care about the safety of every single person in the state of Texas , \"","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"O ' Rourke said .","depth":14},{"id":118,"text":"\" No wall is going to solve legitimate security concerns ,","depth":14},{"id":119,"text":"but smart policy will . \"","depth":14},{"id":120,"text":"Throughout the debate , Cruz called O ' Rourke \" extreme , \"","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"saying","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"he was to the left of Bernie Sanders .","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"There ' s a strategy to this ;","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"as Texas political scientist James Henson told ' s Tara Golshan ,","depth":14},{"id":125,"text":"Cruz is trying to define O ' Rourke negatively","depth":14},{"id":126,"text":"because his name ID is still relatively low","depth":14},{"id":127,"text":"compared to the Republican senators .","depth":14},{"id":128,"text":"One of the repeated attacks","depth":14},{"id":129,"text":"Cruz has lobbed at O ' Rourke","depth":14},{"id":130,"text":"is that he would be weak on crime","depth":14},{"id":131,"text":"and not support law enforcement .","depth":14},{"id":132,"text":"That was something","depth":14},{"id":133,"text":"O ' Rourke seemed eager to address on Tuesday ;","depth":14},{"id":134,"text":"he highlighted his support for local law enforcement multiple times .","depth":13},{"id":135,"text":"3 ) The debate showed two candidates","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"still trying to appeal to the Democratic and Republican bases","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"Fundamentally , O ' Rourke and Cruz ' s messaging","depth":13},{"id":138,"text":"- and the voters","depth":14},{"id":139,"text":"they ' re trying to appeal to -","depth":14},{"id":140,"text":"hasn ' t really changed","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"since they first started campaigning .","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"Cruz is very much appealing to the state ' s conservative base","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"by attempting to paint his opponent as somewhat of a left-wing boogeyman .","depth":12},{"id":144,"text":"And he has good reason to :","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"Older , whiter voters in Texas are more likely to turn out , and more likely to vote Republican .","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"So , predictably , Cruz hit at that message again on Tuesday .","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"As the men debated health care and O ' Rourke ' s support for Medicare-for-all ,","depth":10},{"id":148,"text":"Cruz suggested","depth":11},{"id":149,"text":"that O ' Rourke wanted to add illegal immigrants to the program ,","depth":12},{"id":150,"text":"thus taking it away from senior citizens .","depth":12},{"id":151,"text":"\" The cost would be immense , \"","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"Cruz said .","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"\" He wants to put everyone","depth":12},{"id":154,"text":"who hasn ' t paid into Medicare on Medicare .","depth":12},{"id":155,"text":"That would bankrupt Medicare . \"","depth":11},{"id":156,"text":"O ' Rourke is making a noticeable effort","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"to reach out to the state ' s nonwhite populations","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"- notably African Americans and Latinos -","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"by talking about police brutality , race relations , and the importance of immigrants in the United States .","depth":9},{"id":160,"text":"It ' s something","depth":10},{"id":161,"text":"he brought up in the first Senate debate in September","depth":11},{"id":162,"text":"but didn ' t mention as much on Tuesday night .","depth":11},{"id":163,"text":"Instead , O ' Rourke focused more on Latino voters ,","depth":10},{"id":164,"text":"reiterating his support for the DREAM Act .","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"O ' Rourke is undoubtedly trying the riskier tactic","depth":10},{"id":166,"text":"to pull off a win in Texas ,","depth":10},{"id":167,"text":"as nonwhite voters","depth":11},{"id":168,"text":"- especially Latino voters -","depth":11},{"id":169,"text":"tend to have much lower voter turnout rates .","depth":10},{"id":170,"text":"Whether they do come out for O ' Rourke in November will tell us","depth":10},{"id":171,"text":"whether something big has changed in the Lone Star State","depth":10},{"id":172,"text":"- or not .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":345,"left":200,"right":344,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":200,"left":180,"right":199,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":180,"left":175,"right":179,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":175,"left":174,"right":2,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":174,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":179,"left":3,"right":178,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":178,"left":4,"right":177,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":177,"left":5,"right":176,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":176,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":199,"left":188,"right":198,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":188,"left":182,"right":187,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":182,"left":181,"right":10,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":181,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":187,"left":11,"right":186,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":186,"left":12,"right":185,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":185,"left":183,"right":184,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":183,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"elaboration",